@startuml data-flow-diagram
title "Infraware Terminal - Data Flow Diagram (Core Loop)"

!define INPUTCOLOR #FFF4E6
!define PROCESSINGCOLOR #E8F4F8
!define OUTPUTCOLOR #E8F8F5
!define STATECOLOR #FFE8E8

skinparam style strictuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam NoteBorderColor #FFD700
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFACD
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor PROCESSINGCOLOR
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #4A90E2

start

:Initialize Terminal;
note on right
    InfrawareTerminal::builder()
    .with_llm_client(...)
    .build()
end note

:Load Aliases Async;
note on right
    tokio::spawn_blocking()
    - System aliases (files)
    - User aliases (.bashrc, etc.)
    - CommandCache populated
end note

:Render Welcome Banner;

:Enter Main Event Loop;

repeat
  :Poll Events (100ms timeout);
  note on right
    EventHandler::poll_event()
    Detects keyboard/terminal events
    Filters Windows duplicate events
  end note

  if (Event Type?) then (Input Char)
    :Add char to InputBuffer;
    note on right
      TerminalState::insert_char(c)
      InputBuffer stores text + cursor pos
      Updates immediately
    end note
  elseif (Delete Char)
    :Remove char from InputBuffer;
  elseif (Move Cursor)
    :Update cursor position in InputBuffer;
  elseif (History Nav)
    :Navigate CommandHistory;
    note on right
      Up: TerminalState::history_previous()
      Down: TerminalState::history_next()
      Load/restore from history
    end note
  elseif (Scroll)
    :Adjust OutputBuffer scroll position;
  elseif (Tab Complete)
    #PROCESSINGCOLOR
    :Handle Tab Completion;
    note on right
      TabCompletionHandler::handle_tab_completion()
      1. Extract partial word from input
      2. Complete command or file path
      3. Update input buffer
    end note
  elseif (Submit)
    #INPUTCOLOR
    :Extract Input from InputBuffer;
    note on right
      Get full text entered by user
      Input ready for classification
    end note

    :Add to CommandHistory;

    :Echo Input to OutputBuffer;
    note on right
      Show user what they typed
      Formatted with color
    end note

    :Sync History to Arc<RwLock>;
    note on right
      Update shared history for
      HistoryExpansionHandler (!!,  !$, etc.)
      With poisoning recovery
    end note

    :Classify Input (SCAN Algorithm);
    #PROCESSINGCOLOR
    note on right
      InputClassifier::classify()
      Alias expansion first
      Then 9-handler chain
    end note

    if (Classification Result?) then (Command)
      #PROCESSINGCOLOR
      :Extract Command + Args;
      note on right
        InputType::Command {
          command,
          args,
          original_input
        }
      end note

      :CommandOrchestrator::handle_command();
      note on right
        Responsibilities:
        1. Check for special commands (clear, reload-aliases)
        2. Verify command exists (skip for shell builtins)
        3. Execute via CommandExecutor
        4. Display output
      end note

      if (Special Built-in?) then (clear)
        :Clear OutputBuffer;
      elseif (reload-aliases)
        :Reload System + User Aliases;
        note on right
          spawn_blocking for async alias reload
          Updates CommandCache
        end note
      else
        :Execute Command (Async);
        note on right
          CommandExecutor::execute()
          - Run with tokio
          - Capture stdout/stderr
          - 30 second timeout
          - Return CommandOutput
        end note

        :Format Output;
        note on right
          MessageFormatter::command()
          Apply ANSI colors
          Handle errors gracefully
        end note

        :Add to OutputBuffer;
        note on right
          TerminalState::add_output()
          Auto-scroll to bottom
          Trim if >10,000 lines
        end note
      endif

    elseif (Natural Language)
      #OUTPUTCOLOR
      :Extract Query Text;

      :NaturalLanguageOrchestrator::handle_query();
      note on right
        Responsibilities:
        1. Show "Querying AI assistant..."
        2. Send to LLM
        3. Render response
        4. Display results
      end note

      :Display Waiting State;
      note on right
        Add info message
        Render UI immediately
        User sees "waiting" indicator
      end note

      :Query LLM (Async);
      note on right
        llm_client.query(query)
        HttpLLMClient for production
        MockLLMClient for testing
        30 second timeout
      end note

      if (LLM Success?) then (Yes)
        :Render Response Markdown;
        note on right
          ResponseRenderer::render_markdown()
          - Parse markdown structure
          - Apply syntax highlighting
          - Convert to ANSI codes
          - Return Vec<String>
        end note

        :Add to OutputBuffer;
      else (Error)
        :Display Error Message;
        note on right
          Format with MessageFormatter::error()
          Show helpful error context
          Suggest alternatives
        end note

        :Add Error to OutputBuffer;
      endif

    elseif (Command Typo)
      #OUTPUTCOLOR
      :Show Typo Suggestion;
      note on right
        InputType::CommandTypo
        Shows suggestion + distance
        Prevents accidental LLM calls
      end note

      :Add to OutputBuffer;

    elseif (Empty)
      #OUTPUTCOLOR
      :Skip (No Output);

    endif

    :Set Mode to Normal;
    note on right
      TerminalMode::Normal
      Ready for next input
    end note

  elseif (Clear Screen)
    #STATECOLOR
    :Clear OutputBuffer;
  elseif (Resize)
    :Trigger Re-render;
    note on right
      Terminal resized
      Let UI handle layout recalculation
      Next render will adapt to new size
    end right
  elseif (Quit)
    #STATECOLOR
    :Exit Main Loop;
    break
  else (Unknown)
    :Ignore Event;
  endif

  :Render Updated State;
  #STATECOLOR
  note on right
    TerminalUI::render(&state)
    - Create new Frame
    - Layout into panes
    - Render output (OutputBuffer)
    - Render input (InputBuffer)
    - Render status bar
    - Display cursor
    - Flush to terminal
  end note

repeat while (Running?)

:Cleanup Terminal;
note on right
  Disable raw mode
  Clear terminal state
  Return to normal shell
end note

:Exit Application;

stop

' Legend and notes
note right of start
    **Main Event Loop** (Simplified):
    1. Poll for terminal event (100ms timeout)
    2. Process event (keyboard, mouse, resize, etc.)
    3. Update TerminalState based on event
    4. Render updated state to screen
    5. Loop until quit requested

    Performance: ~100ms per cycle (timeout-based)
    Input latency: <100ms typical
end note

note bottom
    **Data Flow Key Points**:

    **Alias Expansion**:
    - Pre-classification step
    - Loads at startup async
    - Checked before handler chain

    **SCAN Algorithm** (9-Handler Chain):
    1. EmptyInputHandler - <1μs
    2. HistoryExpansionHandler - <20μs
    3. ShellBuiltinHandler - <1μs
    4. PathCommandHandler - ~10μs
    5. KnownCommandHandler - <1μs (cache hit)
    6. CommandSyntaxHandler - ~10μs
    7. TypoDetectionHandler - ~100μs
    8. NaturalLanguageHandler - ~5μs
    9. DefaultHandler - <1μs

    **Command Execution Path**:
    - InputType::Command → CommandOrchestrator
    - Execute async, capture output
    - Display in OutputBuffer
    - Add to history

    **LLM Query Path**:
    - InputType::NaturalLanguage → NaturalLanguageOrchestrator
    - Query LLM (HttpLLMClient or Mock)
    - Render markdown response
    - Display in OutputBuffer

    **Terminal State Updates**:
    - All changes go through TerminalState
    - State includes 3 buffers + mode
    - After any change, UI re-renders
    - RwLock for thread-safe history access
end note

@enduml
